article.headline: Colorado St. 75, N. Colorado 61
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Wes Eikmeier scored a career-high 17 points to lead Colorado State to a 75-61 victory over Northern Colorado on Monday night. Travis Franklin added 16 points on 12-of-15 shooting for the Rams (5-3), who have beaten the Bears nine consecutive times at home. Andy Ogide had 13 points and Dorian Green 11. Devon Beitzel had a season-high 29 points for Northern Colorado (4-6) which has won only twice in Fort Collins since the 1935-36 season when both programs were members of the Rocky Mountain Athletic Conference. Chris Kaba added 11 points for the Bears, who lost their third in a row.
